---
title: One-Pan Mango Salsa Pork Tacos with Cilantro & Sour Cream
description: The magic ingredient that makes these quick one-pan pork tacos sing is a speedy homemade mango salsa that adds tangy-juicy-tropical goodness to every tasty bite. Tuck that spiced pork into soft flour tacos along with charred pepper and onion, top with a spoonful of mango salsa, and finish with a drizzle of sour cream for a plate that pops.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66019b2bda283ecbc2883d33-6bed5a73.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66019b2bda283ecbc2883d33.pdf
author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: Mexican
course: main course
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-mango-salsa-pork-tacos-66019b2bda283ecbc2883d33
nutrition:
  calories: 800 kcal
  fat: 43 g
  saturated fat: 14 g
  carbohydrates: 68 g
  sugar: 20 g
  protein: 31 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1540 mg
time required: 30 minutes
---

Wash and dry produce.

Drain @mango{4%ounce}, reserving juice in a small #bowl{}; roughly chop mango. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @onion{1}(thinly sliced); mince a few slices until you have 2 TBSP (4 TBSP for 4 servings). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Quarter @lime{1}. Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(into strips).

In a second small bowl, combine mango, minced onion, half the cilantro, and a squeeze of lime juice. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add sliced onion and green pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Reduce to medium heat.

Add @ground pork{10%ounce} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tablespoon} to pan with veggies; season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in mango juice and @Tex-Mex paste{1}; cook until thickened and saucy, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Remove pan from heat and stir in remaining cilantro.

While pork cooks, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp paper towels and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with pork filling. Top with mango salsa and dollop with @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Ground pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.